President Joe Biden has ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff as a mark of respect for Robert Joseph Dole, a statesman and war hero. This order applies to the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government. The flag will be flown at half-staff until sunset on December 9, 2021. The same honor will be observed at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations. The order was signed on December 5, 2021.